Level 452 is the 453rd level of the backrooms. <span class="spoilerblur">The Neon Glowstick Concert calls for you.</span>
== Description==
Level 452 is split into two parts. One of the two parts consists of an empty liminal concert lobby, while the other portrays an outdoor concert. The level as a whole however, is a concert-themed space. The connection between the two parts of the level is unusually connected to each other, making mapping the level nearly, if not completely impossible.
===The lobby===
{{Blurimage|align=Left|width=160px|caption=The lobby of level 452|file=Conlobby1.jpg}} The lobby of level 452 consists of a minimalist lobby with neon aspects, including glowing layouts and the outdoors. The lobby is mainly empty with echoes of every little noise one can make and rare instances with furnishing. The lobby spans across hundreds of feet with some architecture cloning itself across the way. The outside of level 452 seen through the window is seen to be at a constant state of fast-forwarded movement mainly pairing with unusual slow motion. There can be many cheers heard through the thin walls of the concert.{{Blurimage|align=Right|width=160px|caption=Another view of the lobby|file=Conlobby2.jpg}}

Glowsticks can sometimes be claimed by wanderers at the front desks inside vases. Vases may not possess glowsticks inside them, and may be replaced with different forms of liquid including [[Object 1|almond water,]] blood from an unknown source, and, in worst cases, [[Object 12|liquid pain.]] Some glowsticks are found as entity versions. Glowsticks are the only artificial light other than concert lights that can function in the concert.

Playing through the speakers are classical songs that are distorted in weird, deafening ways. Staying in the lobby area for a prolonged amount of time can cause the classical music to shut off abruptly, being replaced with absolute nothingness causing any noise occurring in the concert lobby from any source, simply blocked out.<ref>It is better to think about the sentence as how it feels being completely deaf with the ability to hear nothing.</ref> 

If one manages to find a neon light coated door within the lobby, they shall be transported to the concert area via the door in the lobby. 



===The concert===
{{Blurimage|align=Right|width=140px|caption=The concert area of level 452|file=con1.jpg}}If one manages to go past the lobby area of level 452, they will end up in a concert region of level 452. The concert is a zone after the lobby, expanding the size of roughly two football stadiums, making traversing hard to accomplish. The space between the lobby and the concert section possesses unrealistic geometry, with the lobby area distorting in unusual ways when entering the concert zone. When one enters the concert region, the lobby behind them swiftly relocates, materializing to the other side of the concert.  The song playing within the concert is unrecognizable with no reports stating the song performing to be recognizable or familiar, the song blasts at an earsplitting decibel rate, making wanderers go partly deaf, if one stays for a longer time however, their eardrums will burst open at an unrepairable state.

{{Blurimage|align=Left|width=140px|caption=Closer, deafening, fatal.|file=RealCon3.jpg}}

The main stage in the center of the concert is a pastel purple colored box over a black void, the black void erupts a black smoke every once in a while, that can suffocate and blind wanderers within the section. Though constant singing can be heard in the concert, getting to the view of the stage reveals no main entity or being on the center. It is possible to get up close the stage, though if one does, there is no prevention to deafness. 

Lighting in the concert consists of blue-purple colors and hues that most times focus on one singular area instead of moving around the concert at a swift pace. The lights can affect people with photosensitive epilepsy. Additionally, extra ornamental and air decorations, like confetti, can be spread throughout the level from an unknown source; these decorations are a major choking hazard. There is an open pitch-black sky above the concert consisting of glowing stars and one singular orb of light.<ref>It is unknown what the orb of light is, where it came from, and more unsolved mysterious details about the glowing orb.</ref> Staring at the pitch-black sky can cause eye aches, especially when looking at either both the stars or the moon for a long time.    

Every artificial light but two will be cancelled out.

==Entities ==

=== '''''Smilers''''' ===
Smilers simply live in level 452 in pitch-black dark areas in the lobby zone. Smilers do not appear in the concert area naturally due to the huge presence of light being produced, however in the times where the blackout event occurs, smilers shall appear to be a danger within the darker areas. Smilers disappear within a blink of an eye when the blackout event ends unusually, though not when exposed by manual light used by humans like flashlights.

=== '''''Facelings''''' ===
Facelings are fully devoid in the lobby region, instead being only present in the concert area. Facelings serve little to no purpose, only having the capability of taking up space and being dangerous when only the crowd crush event is occurring. 

=== '''''Alive Glowsticks''''' ===
Alive glowsticks have yet to be classified as real entities, not being tested enough to be alive or not, though it has been agreed that the most fitting category to put alive glowsticks is the entity section. Different to the normal glowsticks, alive glowsticks give off a mild scream within, the scream appears to be distorted in inhumane ways.

Inside the lobby, glowsticks deal no harm as they do in the concert, the only effects the alive glowsticks give off are screams and at some times unable to glow at some times, seemingly powering off randomly for a recorded maximum of an hour. Inside the concert, the alive glowsticks are hard to hold, being described as holding a spiky cylinder. Unusually, the glowstick does not look to change any physical change when in the concert.

Alive glowsticks, unlike regular glowsticks, have a rotting smell that can only be "activated" when being held.

==Consequences==
<div class="tabs vertical">
Level 452 possesses different consequences for staying a long time in the level, with some more survivable than others. <ul class="tabs__caption">

<tabber>
|-| Hypnosis song=
{{Blurimage|align=Right|width=140px|caption=My vision darkens, why? |file=con6.jpg}} The song playing in the level possesses the ability to rarely put some people capable of hearing it to a trance until their hearing is cut off or they are killed or harmed moderately. Trying to snap people out trances forcefully will always come out unsuccessful unless using the previously mentioned ways. Going closer to the main stage will only make the music louder with a more common chance of hypnosis.


During the state anyone is in hypnosis, from what some recalls, their vision gets gradually darker with black fade like an extremely strong vignette. To the view of another wanderer, the one affected by the hypnosis will lose function in their arms while keeping their legs in a rock-hard state, being extremely challenging to budge, though this does not prevent the wanderer from crowd crushes.

The photo given in this section is a remake of what the vignette effect looks like allegedly, the vignette effect was reported to look different to some peoples' memory of experiencing it. 

There is no prevention towards hypnosis, hypnosis only wears off after an approximate of one hour.

|-| Absent photosensitive warnings=
Owing to the flashing neon lights within the concert area, entering the region with photosensitive epilepsy, like mentioned earlier, is heavily not recommended, as it can primarily cause majorly harmful and deadly effects to occur, including seizures. Entities are not affected from the flashing lights.

The symptoms of photosensitive epilepsy within the level are different than the ones in the Frontrooms. Being affected by flashing lights may cause wanderers affected to shake uncontrollably throughout the body, consecutively, however, they are seen to forcibly move to the center of the stage at a rapid pace, though they still can be prevented by many obstacles. The symptoms of photosensitive epilepsy that occur in this level last around 15–20 minutes, unfortunately, effects occur almost immediately.
|-| Crowd crush=
{{Blurimage|align=Left|width=140px|caption="It's getting quite crowded..."|file=con2.jpg}}Crowd crushes can happen in the level when facelings seem to cause an apocalyptic  event where the wanderer gets trampled over, causing lack of breath, physical damage, or death, much like what happens in some real life cases. Only the wanderers seem to be affected by the crowd crush event, with entities not affected by crowd crushes.


Should one get caught in a crowd crush, forcefully push your way up by shoving facelings and other entities and containing your balance, staying calm will only make the entities attack more while one is on the ground. Do not attempt to make noise or panic while caught in a crowd crush.
|-| Blackouts=
{{Blurimage|align=right|width=140px|caption=Sudden darkness spreading.|file=ConcertBlackout.webp}} In random, indefinite times in level 452, blackouts can occur. The blackout event, when activating, blow a piercing high pitch throughout the level, after the buzz, all lights but one will abruptly shut down, including glowsticks. The level will become significantly quieter along with the darkness with noises instantly cutting off the moment the event transpires. The layout of the concert and position of some regions in the concert, like the entrance to the moved lobby, will not be affected or changed once the blackout happens.


Although the darkness does not usually cause insanity inside the people who are caught in the event, it does activate some feeling of unease and paranoia, with some having the sudden urge to be defensive suddenly. 

Once the blackout event happens, the open pitch-black sky above the concert suddenly casts a faint white light down onto the concert paired with a buzzing noise. The light is said to be both small and hard to look at without any eye pain, consequently, submerging your entire body in the light can cause your skin to reach high temperatures, reaching second degree burns if stood in for too long. The orb of light and the stars in the sky, once the blackout event occurs, radiate a glow brighter than when the event does not occur.
</tabber>

